{
  "video_id": "38OUCtzkT4Q",
  "title": "How early life experience is written into DNA | Moshe Szyf",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12740.0,
      "end_time": 14424.0,
      "text": "So it all came to life"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14448.0,
      "end_time": 16280.0,
      "text": "in a dark bar in Madrid."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16843.0,
      "end_time": 21670.0,
      "text": "I encountered my colleague from McGill, Michael Meaney."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21910.0,
      "end_time": 23396.0,
      "text": "And we were drinking a few beers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23420.0,
      "end_time": 25473.0,
      "text": "and like scientists do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25497.0,
      "end_time": 26943.0,
      "text": "he told me about his work."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 28124.0,
      "end_time": 35770.0,
      "text": "And he told me that he is interested in how mother rats lick their pups"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35102.0,
      "end_time": 36471.0,
      "text": "after they were born."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 37476.0,
      "end_time": 39894.0,
      "text": "And I was sitting there and saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39919.0,
      "end_time": 42919.0,
      "text": "\"This is where my tax dollars are wasted --"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 42943.0,
      "end_time": 43977.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44100.0,
      "end_time": 46779.0,
      "text": "on this kind of soft science.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47655.0,
      "end_time": 50152.0,
      "text": "And he started telling me"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 50176.0,
      "end_time": 53576.0,
      "text": "that the rats, like humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 53600.0,
      "end_time": 56460.0,
      "text": "lick their pups in very different ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 56700.0,
      "end_time": 58805.0,
      "text": "Some mothers do a lot of that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58829.0,
      "end_time": 61340.0,
      "text": "some mothers do very little,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61580.0,
      "end_time": 63280.0,
      "text": "and most are in between."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63687.0,
      "end_time": 65588.0,
      "text": "But what&#39;s interesting about it"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65612.0,
      "end_time": 70530.0,
      "text": "is when he follows these pups when they become adults --"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 70554.0,
      "end_time": 74733.0,
      "text": "like, years in human life, long after their mother died."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74757.0,
      "end_time": 76825.0,
      "text": "They are completely different animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 76849.0,
      "end_time": 81222.0,
      "text": "The animals that were licked and groomed heavily,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 81246.0,
      "end_time": 82997.0,
      "text": "the high-licking and grooming,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 83879.0,
      "end_time": 85243.0,
      "text": "are not stressed."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 85842.0,
      "end_time": 88910.0,
      "text": "They have different sexual behavior."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 88115.0,
      "end_time": 91700.0,
      "text": "They have a different way of living"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 91940.0,
      "end_time": 96574.0,
      "text": "than those that were not treated as intensively by their mothers."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 97754.0,
      "end_time": 100918.0,
      "text": "So then I was thinking to myself:"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 100942.0,
      "end_time": 102234.0,
      "text": "Is this magic?"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 102822.0,
      "end_time": 104191.0,
      "text": "How does this work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 104215.0,
      "end_time": 106424.0,
      "text": "As geneticists would like you to think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 107210.0,
      "end_time": 111181.0,
      "text": "perhaps the mother had the \"bad mother\" gene"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 111206.0,
      "end_time": 114843.0,
      "text": "that caused her pups to be stressful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 114867.0,
      "end_time": 117414.0,
      "text": "and then it was passed from generation to generation;"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 117438.0,
      "end_time": 120138.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s all determined by genetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 120162.0,
      "end_time": 123656.0,
      "text": "Or is it possible that something else is going on here?"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 123680.0,
      "end_time": 127251.0,
      "text": "In rats, we can ask this question and answer it."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127275.0,
      "end_time": 130880.0,
      "text": "So what we did is a cross-fostering experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 130904.0,
      "end_time": 135659.0,
      "text": "You essentially separate the litter, the babies of this rat, at birth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 135683.0,
      "end_time": 137549.0,
      "text": "to two kinds of fostering mothers --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137574.0,
      "end_time": 140902.0,
      "text": "not the real mothers, but mothers that will take care of them:"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 140926.0,
      "end_time": 143179.0,
      "text": "high-licking mothers and low-licking mothers."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143204.0,
      "end_time": 147820.0,
      "text": "And you can do the opposite with the low-licking pups."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 147528.0,
      "end_time": 149900.0,
      "text": "And the remarkable answer was,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 149925.0,
      "end_time": 153964.0,
      "text": "it wasn&#39;t important what gene you got from your mother."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 153988.0,
      "end_time": 159736.0,
      "text": "It was not the biological mother that defined this property of these rats."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 159760.0,
      "end_time": 163766.0,
      "text": "It is the mother that took care of the pups."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 164591.0,
      "end_time": 167416.0,
      "text": "So how can this work?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 168741.0,
      "end_time": 170544.0,
      "text": "I am an a epigeneticist."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 170568.0,
      "end_time": 174240.0,
      "text": "I am interested in how genes are marked"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 174264.0,
      "end_time": 175980.0,
      "text": "by a chemical mark"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 176400.0,
      "end_time": 180809.0,
      "text": "during embryogenesis, during the time we&#39;re in the womb of our mothers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 180833.0,
      "end_time": 183312.0,
      "text": "and decide which gene will be expressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 183336.0,
      "end_time": 184518.0,
      "text": "in what tissue."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 184542.0,
      "end_time": 188712.0,
      "text": "Different genes are expressed in the brain than in the liver and the eye."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 189538.0,
      "end_time": 192377.0,
      "text": "And we thought: Is it possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 192401.0,
      "end_time": 199348.0,
      "text": "that the mother is somehow reprogramming the gene of her offspring"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 199372.0,
      "end_time": 200921.0,
      "text": "through her behavior?"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 200945.0,
      "end_time": 202555.0,
      "text": "And we spent 10 years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 202580.0,
      "end_time": 206621.0,
      "text": "and we found that there is a cascade of biochemical events"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 206645.0,
      "end_time": 210880.0,
      "text": "by which the licking and grooming of the mother, the care of the mother,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 210112.0,
      "end_time": 212595.0,
      "text": "is translated to biochemical signals"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 212619.0,
      "end_time": 215930.0,
      "text": "that go into the nucleus and into the DNA"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 215954.0,
      "end_time": 218320.0,
      "text": "and program it differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 218560.0,
      "end_time": 222952.0,
      "text": "So now the animal can prepare itself for life:"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 222976.0,
      "end_time": 225597.0,
      "text": "Is life going to be harsh?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 225621.0,
      "end_time": 227383.0,
      "text": "Is there going to be a lot of food?"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 227407.0,
      "end_time": 229932.0,
      "text": "Are there going to be a lot of cats and snakes around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 229956.0,
      "end_time": 232279.0,
      "text": "or will I live in an upper-class neighborhood"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 232303.0,
      "end_time": 235100.0,
      "text": "where all I have to do is behave well and proper,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 235340.0,
      "end_time": 238168.0,
      "text": "and that will gain me social acceptance?"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 238798.0,
      "end_time": 244389.0,
      "text": "And now one can think about how important that process can be"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 244413.0,
      "end_time": 245588.0,
      "text": "for our lives."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 245612.0,
      "end_time": 248524.0,
      "text": "We inherit our DNA from our ancestors."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 249231.0,
      "end_time": 251160.0,
      "text": "The DNA is old."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 251184.0,
      "end_time": 253252.0,
      "text": "It evolved during evolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 253758.0,
      "end_time": 258910.0,
      "text": "But it doesn&#39;t tell us if you are going to be born in Stockholm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 258115.0,
      "end_time": 261501.0,
      "text": "where the days are long in the summer and short in the winter,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 261524.0,
      "end_time": 262830.0,
      "text": "or in Ecuador,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 262854.0,
      "end_time": 266387.0,
      "text": "where there&#39;s an equal number of hours for day and night all year round."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 266411.0,
      "end_time": 270206.0,
      "text": "And that has such an enormous [effect] on our physiology."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 271309.0,
      "end_time": 275545.0,
      "text": "So what we suggest is, perhaps what happens early in life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 275569.0,
      "end_time": 277736.0,
      "text": "those signals that come through the mother,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 277760.0,
      "end_time": 282275.0,
      "text": "tell the child what kind of social world you&#39;re going to be living in."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 282299.0,
      "end_time": 285698.0,
      "text": "It will be harsh, and you&#39;d better be anxious and be stressful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 285723.0,
      "end_time": 288846.0,
      "text": "or it&#39;s going to be an easy world, and you have to be different."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 288870.0,
      "end_time": 292600.0,
      "text": "Is it going to be a world with a lot of light or little light?"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 292840.0,
      "end_time": 296690.0,
      "text": "Is it going to be a world with a lot of food or little food?"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 296930.0,
      "end_time": 297617.0,
      "text": "If there&#39;s no food around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 297641.0,
      "end_time": 302257.0,
      "text": "you&#39;d better develop your brain to binge whenever you see a meal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 302281.0,
      "end_time": 307370.0,
      "text": "or store every piece of food that you have as fat."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 308639.0,
      "end_time": 310690.0,
      "text": "So this is good."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 310930.0,
      "end_time": 311950.0,
      "text": "Evolution has selected this"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 311974.0,
      "end_time": 316870.0,
      "text": "to allow our fixed, old DNA to function in a dynamic way"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 316894.0,
      "end_time": 318743.0,
      "text": "in new environments."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 319197.0,
      "end_time": 321780.0,
      "text": "But sometimes things can go wrong;"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 322526.0,
      "end_time": 326388.0,
      "text": "for example, if you&#39;re born to a poor family"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 326412.0,
      "end_time": 329340.0,
      "text": "and the signals are, \"You better binge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 329365.0,
      "end_time": 332580.0,
      "text": "you better eat every piece of food you&#39;re going to encounter.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 332604.0,
      "end_time": 334856.0,
      "text": "But now we humans and our brain have evolved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 334880.0,
      "end_time": 336976.0,
      "text": "have changed evolution even faster."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 337000.0,
      "end_time": 340364.0,
      "text": "Now you can buy McDonald&#39;s for one dollar."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 340388.0,
      "end_time": 346798.0,
      "text": "And therefore, the preparation that we had by our mothers"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 346822.0,
      "end_time": 349414.0,
      "text": "is turning out to be maladaptive."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 350171.0,
      "end_time": 354384.0,
      "text": "The same preparation that was supposed to protect us from hunger and famine"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 354408.0,
      "end_time": 356865.0,
      "text": "is going to cause obesity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 356889.0,
      "end_time": 359859.0,
      "text": "cardiovascular problems and metabolic disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 360486.0,
      "end_time": 363957.0,
      "text": "So this concept that genes could be marked by our experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 363982.0,
      "end_time": 366283.0,
      "text": "and especially the early life experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 366307.0,
      "end_time": 369121.0,
      "text": "can provide us a unifying explanation"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 369145.0,
      "end_time": 371488.0,
      "text": "of both health and disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 372432.0,
      "end_time": 374790.0,
      "text": "But is true only for rats?"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 374814.0,
      "end_time": 377766.0,
      "text": "The problem is, we cannot test this in humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 377790.0,
      "end_time": 381902.0,
      "text": "because ethically, we cannot administer child adversity in a random way."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 381926.0,
      "end_time": 385229.0,
      "text": "So if a poor child develops a certain property,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 385254.0,
      "end_time": 388993.0,
      "text": "we don&#39;t know whether this is caused by poverty"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 389170.0,
      "end_time": 391841.0,
      "text": "or whether poor people have bad genes."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 391865.0,
      "end_time": 394980.0,
      "text": "So geneticists will try to tell you that poor people are poor"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 395400.0,
      "end_time": 397600.0,
      "text": "because their genes make them poor."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 397840.0,
      "end_time": 399440.0,
      "text": "Epigeneticists will tell you"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 399680.0,
      "end_time": 403178.0,
      "text": "poor people are in a bad environment or an impoverished environment"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 403202.0,
      "end_time": 406166.0,
      "text": "that creates that phenotype, that property."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 407396.0,
      "end_time": 413238.0,
      "text": "So we moved to look into our cousins, the monkeys."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 413907.0,
      "end_time": 417601.0,
      "text": "My colleague, Stephen Suomi, has been rearing monkeys"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 417625.0,
      "end_time": 418786.0,
      "text": "in two different ways:"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 418810.0,
      "end_time": 421711.0,
      "text": "randomly separated the monkey from the mother"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 421735.0,
      "end_time": 424327.0,
      "text": "and reared her with a nurse"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 424351.0,
      "end_time": 427310.0,
      "text": "and surrogate motherhood conditions."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 427334.0,
      "end_time": 430500.0,
      "text": "So these monkeys didn&#39;t have a mother; they had a nurse."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 430290.0,
      "end_time": 434649.0,
      "text": "And other monkeys were reared with their normal, natural mothers."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 434673.0,
      "end_time": 439369.0,
      "text": "And when they were old, they were completely different animals."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 439393.0,
      "end_time": 442486.0,
      "text": "The monkeys that had a mother did not care about alcohol,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 442510.0,
      "end_time": 444188.0,
      "text": "they were not sexually aggressive."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 444213.0,
      "end_time": 447980.0,
      "text": "The monkeys that didn&#39;t have a mother were aggressive, were stressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 448400.0,
      "end_time": 449618.0,
      "text": "and were alcoholics."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 450302.0,
      "end_time": 455784.0,
      "text": "So we looked at their DNA early after birth, to see:"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 455808.0,
      "end_time": 458575.0,
      "text": "Is it possible that the mother is marking?"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 458599.0,
      "end_time": 463957.0,
      "text": "Is there a signature of the mother in the DNA of the offspring?"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 463981.0,
      "end_time": 466233.0,
      "text": "These are Day-14 monkeys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 466257.0,
      "end_time": 470333.0,
      "text": "and what you see here is the modern way by which we study epigenetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 470357.0,
      "end_time": 475200.0,
      "text": "We can now map those chemical marks, which we call methylation marks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 475440.0,
      "end_time": 478301.0,
      "text": "on DNA at a single nucleotide resolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 478326.0,
      "end_time": 480203.0,
      "text": "We can map the entire genome."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 480227.0,
      "end_time": 483294.0,
      "text": "We can now compare the monkey that had a mother or not."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 483318.0,
      "end_time": 485272.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s a visual presentation of this."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 485296.0,
      "end_time": 490330.0,
      "text": "What you see is the genes that got more methylated are red."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 490570.0,
      "end_time": 493710.0,
      "text": "The genes that got less methylated are green."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 493950.0,
      "end_time": 495579.0,
      "text": "You can see many genes are changing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 495603.0,
      "end_time": 498317.0,
      "text": "because not having a mother is not just one thing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 498341.0,
      "end_time": 499872.0,
      "text": "it affects the whole way;"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 499896.0,
      "end_time": 503404.0,
      "text": "it sends signals about the whole way your world is going to look"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 503428.0,
      "end_time": 505187.0,
      "text": "when you become an adult."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 505211.0,
      "end_time": 507632.0,
      "text": "And you can see the two groups of monkeys"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 507656.0,
      "end_time": 510376.0,
      "text": "extremely well-separated from each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 511212.0,
      "end_time": 513341.0,
      "text": "How early does this develop?"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 513898.0,
      "end_time": 516111.0,
      "text": "These monkeys already didn&#39;t see their mothers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 516135.0,
      "end_time": 517833.0,
      "text": "so they had a social experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 517857.0,
      "end_time": 522122.0,
      "text": "Do we sense our social status, even at the moment of birth?"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 522951.0,
      "end_time": 527000.0,
      "text": "So in this experiment, we took placentas of monkeys"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 527240.0,
      "end_time": 528981.0,
      "text": "that had different social status."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 529518.0,
      "end_time": 534892.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s interesting about social rank is that across all living beings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 534916.0,
      "end_time": 537534.0,
      "text": "they will structure themselves by hierarchy."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 538165.0,
      "end_time": 540353.0,
      "text": "Monkey number one is the boss;"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 540377.0,
      "end_time": 542714.0,
      "text": "monkey number four is the peon."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 542739.0,
      "end_time": 545178.0,
      "text": "You put four monkeys in a cage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 545202.0,
      "end_time": 548213.0,
      "text": "there will always be a boss and always be a peon."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 549268.0,
      "end_time": 553116.0,
      "text": "And what&#39;s interesting is that the monkey number one"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 553140.0,
      "end_time": 556572.0,
      "text": "is much healthier than monkey number four."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 556596.0,
      "end_time": 558400.0,
      "text": "And if you put them in a cage,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 558424.0,
      "end_time": 563121.0,
      "text": "monkey number one will not eat as much."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 563145.0,
      "end_time": 564982.0,
      "text": "Monkey number four will eat [a lot]."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 565949.0,
      "end_time": 570222.0,
      "text": "And what you see here in this methylation mapping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 570246.0,
      "end_time": 573210.0,
      "text": "a dramatic separation at birth"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 573450.0,
      "end_time": 575759.0,
      "text": "of the animals that had a high social status"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 575783.0,
      "end_time": 578457.0,
      "text": "versus the animals that did not have a high status."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 579169.0,
      "end_time": 583400.0,
      "text": "So we are born already knowing the social information,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 583424.0,
      "end_time": 586477.0,
      "text": "and that social information is not bad or good,"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 586501.0,
      "end_time": 587920.0,
      "text": "it just prepares us for life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 587944.0,
      "end_time": 592185.0,
      "text": "because we have to program our biology differently"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 592209.0,
      "end_time": 595290.0,
      "text": "if we are in the high or the low social status."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 596146.0,
      "end_time": 598260.0,
      "text": "But how can you study this in humans?"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 598530.0,
      "end_time": 601978.0,
      "text": "We can&#39;t do experiments, we can&#39;t administer adversity to humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 602200.0,
      "end_time": 604594.0,
      "text": "But God does experiments with humans,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 604619.0,
      "end_time": 606907.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s called natural disasters."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 606931.0,
      "end_time": 611191.0,
      "text": "One of the hardest natural disasters in Canadian history"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 611215.0,
      "end_time": 613625.0,
      "text": "happened in my province of Quebec."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 613649.0,
      "end_time": 616520.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the ice storm of 1998."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 616760.0,
      "end_time": 619876.0,
      "text": "We lost our entire electrical grid because of an ice storm"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 619900.0,
      "end_time": 622896.0,
      "text": "when the temperatures were, in the dead of winter in Quebec,"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 622921.0,
      "end_time": 624870.0,
      "text": "minus 20 to minus 30."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 624894.0,
      "end_time": 627426.0,
      "text": "And there were pregnant mothers during that time."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 627902.0,
      "end_time": 633934.0,
      "text": "And my colleague Suzanne King followed the children of these mothers"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 633958.0,
      "end_time": 635672.0,
      "text": "for 15 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 636385.0,
      "end_time": 640631.0,
      "text": "And what happened was, that as the stress increased --"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 640655.0,
      "end_time": 643262.0,
      "text": "and here we had objective measures of stress:"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 643287.0,
      "end_time": 647725.0,
      "text": "How long were you without power? Where did you spend your time?"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 647749.0,
      "end_time": 652752.0,
      "text": "Was it in your mother-in-law&#39;s apartment or in some posh country home?"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 652776.0,
      "end_time": 655434.0,
      "text": "So all of these added up to a social stress scale,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 655458.0,
      "end_time": 656839.0,
      "text": "and you can ask the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 656864.0,
      "end_time": 659908.0,
      "text": "How did the children look?"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 659932.0,
      "end_time": 662566.0,
      "text": "And it appears that as stress increases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 662590.0,
      "end_time": 664648.0,
      "text": "the children develop more autism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 664672.0,
      "end_time": 667211.0,
      "text": "they develop more metabolic diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 667235.0,
      "end_time": 670670.0,
      "text": "and they develop more autoimmune diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 670607.0,
      "end_time": 673310.0,
      "text": "We would map the methylation state,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 673550.0,
      "end_time": 678593.0,
      "text": "and again, you see the green genes becoming red as stress increases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 678617.0,
      "end_time": 682108.0,
      "text": "the red genes becoming green as stress increases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 682133.0,
      "end_time": 686683.0,
      "text": "an entire rearrangement of the genome in response to stress."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 689262.0,
      "end_time": 692470.0,
      "text": "So if we can program genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 692495.0,
      "end_time": 696468.0,
      "text": "if we are not just the slaves of the history of our genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 696492.0,
      "end_time": 699120.0,
      "text": "that they could be programmed, can we deprogram them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 699913.0,
      "end_time": 704495.0,
      "text": "Because epigenetic causes can cause diseases like cancer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 705479.0,
      "end_time": 707282.0,
      "text": "metabolic disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 707306.0,
      "end_time": 709409.0,
      "text": "and mental health diseases."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 709940.0,
      "end_time": 712633.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s talk about cocaine addiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 713395.0,
      "end_time": 716451.0,
      "text": "Cocaine addiction is a terrible situation"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 716475.0,
      "end_time": 720242.0,
      "text": "that can lead to death and to loss of human life."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 721365.0,
      "end_time": 723290.0,
      "text": "We asked the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 723314.0,
      "end_time": 726553.0,
      "text": "Can we reprogram the addicted brain"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 726577.0,
      "end_time": 731501.0,
      "text": "to make that animal not addicted anymore?"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 732197.0,
      "end_time": 736477.0,
      "text": "We used a cocaine addiction model"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 736501.0,
      "end_time": 738590.0,
      "text": "that recapitulates what happens in humans."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 738614.0,
      "end_time": 741282.0,
      "text": "In humans, you&#39;re in high school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 741306.0,
      "end_time": 743386.0,
      "text": "some friends suggest you use some cocaine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 743410.0,
      "end_time": 745216.0,
      "text": "you take cocaine, nothing happens."
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 745240.0,
      "end_time": 749441.0,
      "text": "Months pass by, something reminds you of what happened the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 749465.0,
      "end_time": 751105.0,
      "text": "a pusher pushes cocaine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 751129.0,
      "end_time": 753961.0,
      "text": "and you become addicted and your life has changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 753985.0,
      "end_time": 755631.0,
      "text": "In rats, we do the same thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 755655.0,
      "end_time": 757230.0,
      "text": "My colleague, Gal Yadid,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 757254.0,
      "end_time": 760254.0,
      "text": "he trains the animals to get used to cocaine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 760278.0,
      "end_time": 763406.0,
      "text": "then for one month, no cocaine."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 763430.0,
      "end_time": 767106.0,
      "text": "Then he reminds them of the party when they saw the cocaine the first time"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 767130.0,
      "end_time": 769946.0,
      "text": "by cue, the colors of the cage when they saw cocaine."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 769970.0,
      "end_time": 771622.0,
      "text": "And they go crazy."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 771646.0,
      "end_time": 774930.0,
      "text": "They will press the lever to get cocaine"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 774117.0,
      "end_time": 775376.0,
      "text": "until they die."
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 775867.0,
      "end_time": 780310.0,
      "text": "We first determined that the difference between these animals"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 780334.0,
      "end_time": 783350.0,
      "text": "is that during that time when nothing happens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 783590.0,
      "end_time": 784831.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s no cocaine around,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 784855.0,
      "end_time": 786776.0,
      "text": "their epigenome is rearranged."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 786800.0,
      "end_time": 789689.0,
      "text": "Their genes are re-marked in a different way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 789713.0,
      "end_time": 793454.0,
      "text": "and when the cue comes, their genome is ready"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 793479.0,
      "end_time": 795768.0,
      "text": "to develop this addictive phenotype."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 796385.0,
      "end_time": 803155.0,
      "text": "So we treated these animals with drugs that either increase DNA methylation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 803179.0,
      "end_time": 805403.0,
      "text": "which was the epigenetic marker to look at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 805427.0,
      "end_time": 808910.0,
      "text": "or decrease epigenetic markings."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 808934.0,
      "end_time": 812189.0,
      "text": "And we found that if we increased methylation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 812213.0,
      "end_time": 814960.0,
      "text": "these animals go even crazier."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 814120.0,
      "end_time": 816604.0,
      "text": "They become more craving for cocaine."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 816628.0,
      "end_time": 820540.0,
      "text": "But if we reduce the DNA methylation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 820780.0,
      "end_time": 822182.0,
      "text": "the animals are not addicted anymore."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 822206.0,
      "end_time": 823825.0,
      "text": "We have reprogrammed them."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 823849.0,
      "end_time": 827155.0,
      "text": "And a fundamental difference between an epigenetic drug"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 827179.0,
      "end_time": 828485.0,
      "text": "and any other drug"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 828509.0,
      "end_time": 830681.0,
      "text": "is that with epigenetic drugs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 830705.0,
      "end_time": 834837.0,
      "text": "we essentially remove the signs of experience,"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 834861.0,
      "end_time": 836988.0,
      "text": "and once they&#39;re gone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 837120.0,
      "end_time": 840320.0,
      "text": "they will not come back unless you have the same experience."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 840570.0,
      "end_time": 841711.0,
      "text": "The animal now is reprogrammed."
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 841735.0,
      "end_time": 845956.0,
      "text": "So when we visited the animals 30 days, 60 days later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 845980.0,
      "end_time": 848899.0,
      "text": "which is in human terms many years of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 848923.0,
      "end_time": 854229.0,
      "text": "they were still not addicted -- by a single epigenetic treatment."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 856292.0,
      "end_time": 859563.0,
      "text": "So what did we learn about DNA?"
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 859587.0,
      "end_time": 862712.0,
      "text": "DNA is not just a sequence of letters;"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 862736.0,
      "end_time": 864855.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s not just a script."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 864879.0,
      "end_time": 867250.0,
      "text": "DNA is a dynamic movie."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 868187.0,
      "end_time": 873980.0,
      "text": "Our experiences are being written into this movie, which is interactive."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 873122.0,
      "end_time": 876675.0,
      "text": "You&#39;re, like, watching a movie of your life, with the DNA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 876699.0,
      "end_time": 878481.0,
      "text": "with your remote control."
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 878505.0,
      "end_time": 881894.0,
      "text": "You can remove an actor and add an actor."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 882692.0,
      "end_time": 888587.0,
      "text": "And so you have, in spite of the deterministic nature of genetics,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 888611.0,
      "end_time": 892300.0,
      "text": "you have control of the way your genes look,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 892324.0,
      "end_time": 895593.0,
      "text": "and this has a tremendous optimistic message"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 895618.0,
      "end_time": 899126.0,
      "text": "for the ability to now encounter some of the deadly diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 899150.0,
      "end_time": 902540.0,
      "text": "like cancer, mental health,"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 902780.0,
      "end_time": 905600.0,
      "text": "with a new approach,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 905300.0,
      "end_time": 907564.0,
      "text": "looking at them as maladaptation."
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 907588.0,
      "end_time": 910661.0,
      "text": "And if we can epigenetically intervene,"
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 910686.0,
      "end_time": 914182.0,
      "text": "[we can] reverse the movie by removing an actor"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 914206.0,
      "end_time": 917630.0,
      "text": "and setting up a new narrative."
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 917848.0,
      "end_time": 920344.0,
      "text": "So what I told you today is,"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 920369.0,
      "end_time": 925461.0,
      "text": "our DNA is really combined of two components,"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 925485.0,
      "end_time": 927310.0,
      "text": "two layers of information."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 927926.0,
      "end_time": 931601.0,
      "text": "One layer of information is old,"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 931625.0,
      "end_time": 935130.0,
      "text": "evolved from millions of years of evolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 935154.0,
      "end_time": 938330.0,
      "text": "It is fixed and very hard to change."
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 939231.0,
      "end_time": 943810.0,
      "text": "The other layer of information is the epigenetic layer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 943105.0,
      "end_time": 947000.0,
      "text": "which is open and dynamic"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 947240.0,
      "end_time": 951616.0,
      "text": "and sets up a narrative that is interactive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 951640.0,
      "end_time": 958428.0,
      "text": "that allows us to control, to a large extent, our destiny,"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 959515.0,
      "end_time": 962971.0,
      "text": "to help the destiny of our children"
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 962995.0,
      "end_time": 967150.0,
      "text": "and to hopefully conquer disease"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 967174.0,
      "end_time": 971590.0,
      "text": "and serious health challenges"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 971614.0,
      "end_time": 975225.0,
      "text": "that have plagued humankind for a long time."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 975249.0,
      "end_time": 978642.0,
      "text": "So even though we are determined"
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 978666.0,
      "end_time": 980421.0,
      "text": "by our genes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 980445.0,
      "end_time": 983512.0,
      "text": "we have a degree of freedom"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 983536.0,
      "end_time": 987669.0,
      "text": "that can set up our life to a life of responsibility."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 987693.0,
      "end_time": 988913.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 988937.0,
      "end_time": 993892.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}